fields.value: Data collection of low-cost 3D printed prosthetic hands for evaluation

dsDescriptionValue.value: This dataset includes three different data to evaluate the currently used low-cost prosthetic hands. The first data set includes six open-source 3D printed prosthetic hands files. The files are collected from different websites and stored in the created dataset library. Files are ready for direct 3D printing. The second data set includes the numerical analysis of prosthetic ABS and PLA fingers under different carrying loads. The numerical analyses were carried out by LS-DYNA software. The files can be used for the prosthetic fingersâ€™ evaluation and selection of the proper material. The third data set includes the experimental tensile test of ABS and PLA materials. The mechanical properties are calculated from the results which can be used in manufacturing and designing products from these materials.
